  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to practice solving multiplication problems in which the unknown amount can be the number of groups, the number in each group, or the total. The first three problems have the unknown in each of those locations. The sequence of these problems, the context, and the use of the same factors and product encourages students to use a known fact to find the unknown factor in the <q>how many in each group</q> problem. Students will make the connection between this problem type and division in a future unit. Students are able to choose the representation they use to represent and solve the problems.</p>
  </paragraphs>


